                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/866: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-17T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 17, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. Your despatch No. 2896, March 3rd, 1937. You may reply to the British that
                    this Government agrees that the intention of the Protocol of Signature of the
                    London Naval Treaty, 1936, is that full exchange of information similar to that
                    provided for in the naval treaties of 1922 and 1930 should be continued from
                    January 1 to July 1, or until such time as the Treaty shall come into force, and
                    accordingly this Government will communicate to the signatory Governments on a
                    basis of reciprocity particulars with regard to the completion or acquisition of
                    vessels in the period referred to herein above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
